reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy and tall!
reviews.reviewText: I was torn when I ordered this, I have ordered some things on Amazon that are less then well made. I crossed my fingers and clicked place order.Put together just now and I am amazed! Went together easily, didn't need the included hammer, just my hands. It is super sturdy and will hold a ton of shoes! I also have a basket of dog things on it because I actually ran out of shoes and boots. It's nice to know I have extra room if I spy another pair I have to have!I could get 3 pairs on each shelf by flipping the heel and toe of each pair. It gave me room to stack smaller shoes in the center of each shelf.If you are on the fence just order it, you will be happy!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Not a shelf, Only slats to rest shoes on
reviews.reviewText: Perfect size for where I needed it. But I failed to notice that the shelf part was not solid but slats. That was disappointing but totally my fault. It’s very economical when on sale. It is surprisingly sturdy and easy to assemble. Other than the heels of my shoes sliding between the slats I love it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
reviews.reviewText: The rack was fairly easy to put together. It seems sturdy for now. It was too tall for my liking so I cut it down to one large rack and a 2 stand rack. It looks better in the space I used. I hope it remains sturdy and lasts a while. This is my 5th shoe rack. I'll check back in; in about 6 months or earlier should it not last.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great shoe rack
reviews.reviewText: This rack is great, easy to assemble and very tall, provides lots of storage space. I was even able to use the majority of the racks for a shoe rack for the garage, for outdoor shoes for the family, and use the remainder in our closet for extra shoe storage. It is made of a sturdy plastic, but holds up for what we need it for. The directions were easy to understand and came with all the pieces necessary. It also has an extra peice with 5 hooks that attaches to the side that you can hang extra (light) items on for additional organization. Great shoe rack for the price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for small space
reviews.reviewText: My daughter put this together all by herself very easily and it fits perfectly in the small space she had in her room. Very sturdy and holds a nice amount of shoes.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to assemble, looks great, fits perfectly
reviews.reviewText: It took a little time to assemble because there are many parts, but it wasn’t difficult to do. They included a little hammer, but I didn’t need to use it. I would buy another if I had room for it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This product will surprise you
reviews.reviewText: At first, when you unbox the product you will think there is no way that this shoe rack will accommodate your needs...the parts are all plastic. It seems flimsy, BUT it's engineered in a fashion that makes it quite durable once assembled. That said, I still recommend that you anchor the rack to something solid or position it with a wall on one side as it will tend to sway. It's worth the price. I have mine in the garage to easily reach my on-season, go-to footwear.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Does not hold heels well
reviews.reviewText: Easy put together. Fairly sturdy. Would work well for flats or tennis shoes. Does not hold heels well.

I wanted a metal shoe shelf but this is plastic. I was unsure if I would like it but so far…I like it and it’s holding up well. The rods are cheap light weighted metal. The bad part is the mallet used to put it together didn’t stay together, the head kept falling off so I had to use wood glue to glue the head to the handle so it didn’t fly off as I hammered it together. It probably weights like 5 lbs and I can lift the whole thing with one hand. Will see how long it lasts.
It is sturdy. Easy assemble. It has an extra wooden hammer in the package to facilitate assemble. This is a very good tool to go with.
